OL,3,CJersey's minimum wage will rise to #13
OL,4,Cper hour
OL,6,FJersey's Social Security Minister,
OL,7,FDeputy Lyndsay Feltham, says this is a
OL,8,Fstep towards a living wage with the
OL,9,Fisland's minimum salary to be set at
OL,10,Ftwo thirds of the 2024 median hourly
OL,11,Fpay in April 2026 - estimated to be
OL,12,Faround #14.
OL,14,FShe adds: "The transition to a living
OL,15,Fwage is an important priority of this
OL,16,FGovernment as it directly supports
OL,17,Fmany in our community who are most
OL,18,Flikely to be struggling with the cost
OL,19,Fof living."
